==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flamingo
<hw>Fla*min"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Flamingoes</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Sp. <ets>flamenco</ets>,
cf. Pg. <ets>flamingo</ets>, Prov. <ets>flammant</ets>, F.
<ets>flamant</ets>; prop. a p. pr. meaning <ets>flaming</ets>. So called
in allusion to its color. See <er>Flame</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any bird of the genus <gen>Ph⟦oe⟧nicopterus</gen>. The flamingoes
have webbed feet, very long legs, and a beak bent down as if broken.
Their color is usually red or pink. The American flamingo is <spn>P.
ruber</spn>; the European is <spn>P. antiquorum</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flaminical</ent>⟦br⟧
